events.description: Nerva, suspected of complicity of the death of Domitian, is declared emperor by Senate. The Senate then annuls laws passed by Domitian and orders his statues to be destroyed.
events.html: • 96 – Nerva, suspected of complicity of the death of Domitian, is declared emperor by Senate. The Senate then annuls laws passed by Domitian and orders his statues to be destroyed.[1]

events.description: Siege of Damascus: The Rashidun Arabs under Khalid ibn al-Walid capture Damascus from the Byzantine Empire.
events.html: • 634 – Siege of Damascus: The Rashidun Arabs under Khalid ibn al-Walid capture Damascus from the Byzantine Empire.[2]

events.description: Battle of Poitiers: An English army under the command of Edward the Black Prince defeats a French army and captures King John II.
events.html: • 1356 – Battle of Poitiers: An English army under the command of Edward the Black Prince defeats a French army and captures King John II.[3]

events.description: End of the Siege of Marienburg: The State of the Teutonic Order repulses the joint Polish—Lithuanian forces.
events.html: • 1410 – End of the Siege of Marienburg: The State of the Teutonic Order repulses the joint Polish—Lithuanian forces.[4][5]

events.description: Jamestown is burned to the ground by the forces of Nathaniel Bacon during Bacon's Rebellion.
events.html: • 1676 – Jamestown is burned to the ground by the forces of Nathaniel Bacon during Bacon's Rebellion.

events.description: American Revolutionary War: British forces win a tactically expensive victory over the Continental Army in the First Battle of Saratoga.
events.html: • 1777 – American Revolutionary War: British forces win a tactically expensive victory over the Continental Army in the First Battle of Saratoga.

events.description: The Continental Congress passes the first United States federal budget.
events.html: • 1778 – The Continental Congress passes the first United States federal budget.

events.description: George Washington's Farewell Address is printed across America as an open letter to the public.
events.html: • 1796 – George Washington's Farewell Address is printed across America as an open letter to the public.

events.description: French Revolutionary Wars: French-Dutch victory against the Russians and British in the Battle of Bergen.
events.html: • 1799 – French Revolutionary Wars: French-Dutch victory against the Russians and British in the Battle of Bergen.

events.description: Two French shepherd children, Mélanie Calvat and Maximin Giraud, experience a Marian apparition on a mountaintop near La Salette, France, now known as Our Lady of La Salette.
events.html: • 1846 – Two French shepherd children, Mélanie Calvat and Maximin Giraud, experience a Marian apparition on a mountaintop near La Salette, France, now known as Our Lady of La Salette.[6]

events.description: Annibale de Gasparis discovers the asteroid Massalia from the north dome of the Astronomical Observatory of Capodimonte.
events.html: • 1852 – Annibale de Gasparis discovers the asteroid Massalia from the north dome of the Astronomical Observatory of Capodimonte.[7]

events.description: American Civil War: Union troops under William Rosecrans defeat a Confederate force commanded by Sterling Price.
events.html: • 1862 – American Civil War: Union troops under William Rosecrans defeat a Confederate force commanded by Sterling Price.[8]

events.description: American Civil War: The first day of the Battle of Chickamauga, in northwestern Georgia, the bloodiest two-day battle of the conflict, and the only significant Confederate victory in the war's Western Theater.
events.html: • 1863 – American Civil War: The first day of the Battle of Chickamauga, in northwestern Georgia, the bloodiest two-day battle of the conflict, and the only significant Confederate victory in the war's Western Theater.

events.description: American Civil War: Union troops under Philip Sheridan defeat a Confederate force commanded by Jubal Early. With over 50,000 troops engaged, it was the largest battle fought in the Shenandoah Valley.
events.html: • 1864 – American Civil War: Union troops under Philip Sheridan defeat a Confederate force commanded by Jubal Early. With over 50,000 troops engaged, it was the largest battle fought in the Shenandoah Valley.

events.description: La Gloriosa begins in Spain.
events.html: • 1868 – La Gloriosa begins in Spain.

events.description: Franco-Prussian War: The siege of Paris begins. The city held out for over four months before surrendering.
events.html: • 1870 – Franco-Prussian War: The siege of Paris begins. The city held out for over four months before surrendering.

events.description: In New Zealand, the Electoral Act of 1893 is consented to by the governor, giving all women in New Zealand the right to vote.
events.html: • 1893 – In New Zealand, the Electoral Act of 1893 is consented to by the governor, giving all women in New Zealand the right to vote.

events.description: A stampede at Shiloh Baptist Church in Birmingham, Alabama, leads to the death of 115 attendees.
events.html: • 1902 – A stampede at Shiloh Baptist Church in Birmingham, Alabama, leads to the death of 115 attendees.[9]

events.description: World War I: During the East African Campaign, colonial forces of the Belgian Congo (Force Publique) under the command of Charles Tombeur capture the town of Tabora after heavy fighting.
events.html: • 1916 – World War I: During the East African Campaign, colonial forces of the Belgian Congo (Force Publique) under the command of Charles Tombeur capture the town of Tabora after heavy fighting.

events.description: World War II: The Battle of Kępa Oksywska concludes, with Polish losses reaching roughly 14% of all the forces engaged.
events.html: • 1939 – World War II: The Battle of Kępa Oksywska concludes, with Polish losses reaching roughly 14% of all the forces engaged.

events.description: World War II: Witold Pilecki is voluntarily captured and sent to Auschwitz concentration camp to gather and smuggle out information for the resistance movement.
events.html: • 1940 – World War II: Witold Pilecki is voluntarily captured and sent to Auschwitz concentration camp to gather and smuggle out information for the resistance movement.[10][11]

events.description: World War II: The Battle of Hürtgen Forest begins. It will become the second-longest individual battle that the U.S. Army has ever fought.
events.html: • 1944 – World War II: The Battle of Hürtgen Forest begins. It will become the second-longest individual battle that the U.S. Army has ever fought.[12]

events.description: World War II: The Moscow Armistice between Finland and the Soviet Union is signed, which officially ended the Continuation War.
events.html: • 1944 – World War II: The Moscow Armistice between Finland and the Soviet Union is signed, which officially ended the Continuation War.[13]

events.description: The Council of Europe is founded following a speech by Winston Churchill at the University of Zurich.
events.html: • 1946 – The Council of Europe is founded following a speech by Winston Churchill at the University of Zurich.

events.description: Korean War: An attack by North Korean forces was repelled at the Battle of Nam River.
events.html: • 1950 – Korean War: An attack by North Korean forces was repelled at the Battle of Nam River.[14]

events.description: Indian Prime Minister Jawaharlal Nehru and Pakistani President Ayub Khan sign the Indus Waters Treaty for the control and management of the Indus, Chenab, Jhelum, Ravi, Sutlej and Beas rivers.
events.html: • 1960 – Indian Prime Minister Jawaharlal Nehru and Pakistani President Ayub Khan sign the Indus Waters Treaty for the control and management of the Indus, Chenab, Jhelum, Ravi, Sutlej and Beas rivers.[15]

events.description: Michael Eavis hosts the first Glastonbury Festival.
events.html: • 1970 – Michael Eavis hosts the first Glastonbury Festival.

events.description: Kostas Georgakis, a Greek student of geology, sets himself ablaze in Matteotti Square in Genoa, Italy, as a protest against the dictatorial regime of Georgios Papadopoulos.
events.html: • 1970 – Kostas Georgakis, a Greek student of geology, sets himself ablaze in Matteotti Square in Genoa, Italy, as a protest against the dictatorial regime of Georgios Papadopoulos.

events.description: Turkish Airlines Flight 452 hits the Taurus Mountains, outskirt of Karatepe, Turkey, killing all 154 passengers and crew.
events.html: • 1976 – Turkish Airlines Flight 452 hits the Taurus Mountains, outskirt of Karatepe, Turkey, killing all 154 passengers and crew.

events.description: Two Imperial Iranian Air Force F-4 Phantom II jets fly out to investigate an unidentified flying object.
events.html: • 1976 – Two Imperial Iranian Air Force F-4 Phantom II jets fly out to investigate an unidentified flying object.

events.description: The Solomon Islands join the United Nations.
events.html: • 1978 – The Solomon Islands join the United Nations.

events.description: Scott Fahlman posts the first documented emoticons :-) and :-( on the Carnegie Mellon University bulletin board system.
events.html: • 1982 – Scott Fahlman posts the first documented emoticons :-) and :-( on the Carnegie Mellon University bulletin board system.

events.description: Saint Kitts and Nevis gains its independence.
events.html: • 1983 – Saint Kitts and Nevis gains its independence.[16]

events.description: A strong earthquake kills thousands and destroys about 400 buildings in Mexico City.
events.html: • 1985 – A strong earthquake kills thousands and destroys about 400 buildings in Mexico City.

events.description: Tipper Gore and other political wives form the Parents Music Resource Center as Frank Zappa, John Denver, and other musicians testify at U.S. Congressional hearings on obscenity in rock music.
events.html: • 1985 – Tipper Gore and other political wives form the Parents Music Resource Center as Frank Zappa, John Denver, and other musicians testify at U.S. Congressional hearings on obscenity in rock music.

events.description: A bomb destroys UTA Flight 772 in mid-air above the Tùnùrù Desert, Niger, killing all 170 passengers and crew.
events.html: • 1989 – A bomb destroys UTA Flight 772 in mid-air above the Tùnùrù Desert, Niger, killing all 170 passengers and crew.

events.description: Ötzi the Iceman is discovered in the Alps on the border between Italy and Austria.
events.html: • 1991 – Ötzi the Iceman is discovered in the Alps on the border between Italy and Austria.

events.description: The Washington Post and The New York Times publish the Unabomber manifesto.
events.html: • 1995 – The Washington Post and The New York Times publish the Unabomber manifesto.

events.description: The Guelb El-Kebir massacre in Algeria kills 53 people.
events.html: • 1997 – The Guelb El-Kebir massacre in Algeria kills 53 people.

events.description: The Thai army stages a coup. The Constitution is revoked and martial law is declared.
events.html: • 2006 – The Thai army stages a coup. The Constitution is revoked and martial law is declared.

events.description: A Learjet 60 carrying musicians Travis Barker and Adam "DJ AM" Goldstein crashes during a rejected takeoff from Colombia Metropolitan Airport in West Columbia, South Carolina, killing four of the six people on board. Barker and Goldstein both survive.
events.html: • 2008 – A Learjet 60 carrying musicians Travis Barker and Adam "DJ AM" Goldstein crashes during a rejected takeoff from Colombia Metropolitan Airport in West Columbia, South Carolina, killing four of the six people on board. Barker and Goldstein both survive.[17]

events.description: The leaking oil well in the Deepwater Horizon oil spill is sealed.
events.html: • 2010 – The leaking oil well in the Deepwater Horizon oil spill is sealed.

events.description: Mariano Rivera of the New York Yankees surpasses Trevor Hoffman to become Major League Baseball's all-time career saves leader with 602.
events.html: • 2011 – Mariano Rivera of the New York Yankees surpasses Trevor Hoffman to become Major League Baseball's all-time career saves leader with 602.

events.description: In the wake of a manhunt, the suspect in a series of bombings in New York and New Jersey is apprehended after a shootout with police.
events.html: • 2016 – In the wake of a manhunt, the suspect in a series of bombings in New York and New Jersey is apprehended after a shootout with police.

entities.name: 2016 New York and New Jersey bombings

events.description: The 2017 Puebla earthquake strikes Mexico, causing 370 deaths and over 6,000 injuries, as well as extensive damage.
events.html: • 2017 – The 2017 Puebla earthquake strikes Mexico, causing 370 deaths and over 6,000 injuries, as well as extensive damage.

events.description: A drone strike by the United States kills 30 civilian farmers in Afghanistan.
events.html: • 2019 – A drone strike by the United States kills 30 civilian farmers in Afghanistan.[18]

events.description: The Cumbre Vieja volcano, on the island of La Palma in the Canary Islands, erupts. The eruption lasts for almost three months, ending on December 13.
events.html: • 2021 – The Cumbre Vieja volcano, on the island of La Palma in the Canary Islands, erupts. The eruption lasts for almost three months, ending on December 13.[19]
